      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Reverend John B. Sheerin (1907?-1992) was a Roman Catholic editor, columnist and pioneer in interfaith relations.  A graduate of Fordham University (BA, 1928; JD, 1930), he was editor of <emph render="italic">The Catholic World</emph>, a monthly journal published by the Paulist Fathers, from 1948-1972.  He was an outspoken opponent of the Vietnam War and a supporter of civil rights.  [Adapted from his obituary in the <emph render="italic">New York Times</emph>, 15 Jan 1992.]</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">John B. Sheerin Papers</emph> consists of printed material and writings, much of it editorials from Sheerin's work as editor of <emph render="italic">The Catholic World</emph>, including some indexes to the editorials.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
